00:27:30,182 --> 00:27:32,981
Someone in a research lab
on the floor below screwed up.

496
00:27:33,085 --> 00:27:35,850
Some smallpox virus
managed to float up

497
00:27:35,954 --> 00:27:39,618
through the vents into the
room where she was working.

498
00:27:39,691 --> 00:27:44,686
She died four days later, the last
known person to die from smallpox.

499
00:27:44,830 --> 00:27:48,790
And the person in charge
of the lab was so destroyed,

500
00:27:49,301 --> 00:27:50,860
he killed himself.

501
00:27:52,337 --> 00:27:56,536
Now that he's shedding, I
can't open that door for anyone.

502
00:27:59,945 --> 00:28:01,277
Hey! Look.

503
00:28:01,346 --> 00:28:02,507
There's the proof you need.

504
00:28:02,581 --> 00:28:03,821
There's blood in the urine bag.

505
00:28:03,982 --> 00:28:05,610
His kidneys are shutting down.

506
00:28:05,684 --> 00:28:07,778
He's in the final
stages of the disease.

507
00:28:07,853 --> 00:28:09,879
If smallpox was causing
the kidney failure,

508
00:28:09,955 --> 00:28:11,947
the blood would
be brown. It's red.

509
00:28:12,057 --> 00:28:16,085
Because the kidney cancer is
back and this is not smallpox.

510
00:28:17,863 --> 00:28:19,525
I'm not opening that door.

511
00:28:24,369 --> 00:28:25,735
Well, that makes one of us.

512
00:28:26,238 --> 00:28:27,262
Hey!

513
00:28:29,675 --> 00:28:31,303
Hey! You're insane!

514
00:28:31,376 --> 00:28:32,537
But I'm right.

515
00:28:39,518 --> 00:28:44,081
<i>I hope you are. Because
I can't let you out now.</i>

516
00:28:54,933 --> 00:28:57,562
This is what happens when
you have no respect for authority,

517
00:28:58,370 --> 00:29:00,202
no respect for anything.

518
00:29:00,272 --> 00:29:02,901
You don't think it's a little
much to use the threat of death

519
00:29:02,975 --> 00:29:05,604
to win a totally separate
argument with your boyfriend?

520
00:29:05,711 --> 00:29:08,442
You think this is
about the other thing?

521
00:29:08,780 --> 00:29:10,772
It does seem to track
suspiciously closely.

522
00:29:10,882 --> 00:29:16,116
I don't care right now that you
lied to me. I want you to stay alive.

523
00:29:16,221 --> 00:29:19,214
And if I do, does that
mean I win both arguments?

524
00:29:20,292 --> 00:29:21,783
Put the suit on.

525
00:29:21,893 --> 00:29:23,885
It's unnecessary, Mom.

526
00:29:24,129 --> 00:29:25,859
This is why I didn't
want them telling you.

527
00:29:25,931 --> 00:29:27,593
It's why I'm glad
they didn't tell Wilson.

528
00:29:27,666 --> 00:29:28,964
Dr. House.

529
00:29:38,443 --> 00:29:40,912
I'm getting worse, aren't I?

530
00:29:49,087 --> 00:29:51,249
Interferon takes a
little time to work.

531
00:29:54,660 --> 00:29:55,821
Don't worry.

532
00:30:02,534 --> 00:30:06,869
Tell Broda that I'm increasing his
oxygen. And get my team down here.

533
00:30:23,722 --> 00:30:24,781
Hi.

534
00:30:27,326 --> 00:30:28,658
You're mad at us, aren't you?

535
00:30:28,727 --> 00:30:29,990
Yeah.

536
00:30:30,062 --> 00:30:32,793
Well, you have a right
to be. We weren't honest.

537
00:30:32,864 --> 00:30:34,457
You might not know this yet,

538
00:30:34,533 --> 00:30:37,526
but sometimes adults mess up.

539
00:30:40,739 --> 00:30:44,301
Can I tell you something and
you'll keep it just between us?

540
00:30:46,178 --> 00:30:47,806
I'm not great with kids.

541
00:30:48,080 --> 00:30:50,072
I love them, but I get scared

542
00:30:50,148 --> 00:30:52,913
that I'm gonna do the
wrong thing, and then,

543
00:30:53,218 --> 00:30:54,584
I usually do.

544
00:30:55,587 --> 00:30:58,352
That's what I
did with the lying.

545
00:30:59,424 --> 00:31:02,053
And I'm very sorry about that.

546
00:31:03,762 --> 00:31:06,493
But the reason why
I did the wrong thing

547
00:31:06,565 --> 00:31:10,866
was because I was trying to
get you to do the right thing.

548
00:31:11,837 --> 00:31:16,366
Your mommy and your Lamby
both really need you to get better.

549
00:31:20,045 --> 00:31:23,880
So, do you think that
you could be really brave

550
00:31:26,218 --> 00:31:27,686
and do the right thing?

551
00:31:30,589 --> 00:31:31,784
I'll try.

552
00:31:34,393 --> 00:31:35,452
Great.

553
00:31:37,629 --> 00:31:38,892
Great.

554
00:31:42,300 --> 00:31:46,101
Fever's way up, sats are way
down, pustules still spreading.

555
00:31:46,204 --> 00:31:47,729
Interferon's not working.

556
00:31:47,806 --> 00:31:49,707
Means this is smallpox.

557
00:31:50,041 --> 00:31:54,103
Right, because there are only two
diseases in the whole wide world.

558
00:31:54,212 --> 00:31:55,441
What else could it be?

559
00:31:55,580 --> 00:31:57,105
There's got to be something.

560
00:31:57,215 --> 00:31:58,911
No, there doesn't.

561
00:31:59,050 --> 00:32:01,576
There are still no
pustules on her feet.

562
00:32:01,653 --> 00:32:04,088
All the reasons you thought
it wasn't smallpox still exist.

563
00:32:04,156 --> 00:32:06,421
Forget her feet. Forget
all those other reasons.

564
00:32:06,491 --> 00:32:07,754
Look at him now.

565
00:32:07,826 --> 00:32:09,954
The pox are dome-shaped,
they're on 80% of his body,

566
00:32:10,061 --> 00:32:12,462
and they're not scabbing over.

567
00:32:13,331 --> 00:32:15,391
This is textbook smallpox.

568
00:32:15,767 --> 00:32:18,066
DDx-ing at this point isn't
gonna make a difference.

569
00:32:18,136 --> 00:32:19,263
Don't say that.

570
00:32:19,337 --> 00:32:20,396
I'm sorry.

571
00:32:22,307 --> 00:32:25,675
House, you screwed
up going in there.

572
00:32:41,159 --> 00:32:43,025
You have any fever?

573
00:32:43,528 --> 00:32:44,928
Not yet.

574
00:32:46,932 --> 00:32:48,264
But when it does come,

575
00:32:48,333 --> 00:32:50,165
I assume you'll
see the pettiness

576
00:32:50,235 --> 00:32:52,636
of being mad at me for lying.

577
00:32:52,704 --> 00:32:54,502
Shut up, House.

578
00:33:00,512 --> 00:33:02,538
I'll be right back.

579
00:33:09,821 --> 00:33:12,188
I'm not gonna make it, am I?

580
00:33:24,336 --> 00:33:26,567
You should say
goodbye to your family.

581
00:33:59,838 --> 00:34:01,101
I love you.

582
00:34:01,740 --> 00:34:04,608
Just hold on. Fight this.

583
00:34:06,845 --> 00:34:08,541
You gotta take care of my boy.

584
00:34:12,951 --> 00:34:14,852
No. Promise me.

585
00:34:18,023 --> 00:34:19,514
I promise.

586
00:34:25,530 --> 00:34:27,123
I love you.

587
00:34:27,566 --> 00:34:29,228
I love you, too.

588
00:34:30,735 --> 00:34:32,431
Get Roger closer.

589
00:34:34,706 --> 00:34:36,231
Come closer.

590
00:34:36,474 --> 00:34:37,635
Come on.

591
00:34:40,111 --> 00:34:41,443
Dad?

592
00:34:44,149 --> 00:34:46,050
You're my baby boy.

593
00:34:47,085 --> 00:34:48,883
Dad, please.

594
00:34:50,121 --> 00:34:52,090
It's gonna be okay.

595
00:34:52,591 --> 00:34:54,457
Lulu's gonna take care of you.

596
00:34:54,526 --> 00:34:56,324
I don't want to, Dad.

597
00:34:56,661 --> 00:34:58,254
She's not you.

598
00:35:03,134 --> 00:35:05,501
I will always love you, Rog.

599
00:35:11,343 --> 00:35:12,470
Dad?

600
00:35:15,981 --> 00:35:17,142
Dad!

601
00:36:26,251 --> 00:36:27,480
You're killing me.

602
00:36:27,619 --> 00:36:31,556
The suit will protect you if you
haven't already been exposed.

603
00:36:32,090 --> 00:36:33,649
My air supply's almost out.

604
00:36:33,825 --> 00:36:35,157
<i>We'll give you another canister.</i>

605
00:36:35,260 --> 00:36:37,422
<i>Yeah, and when I
change it, I will be exposed.</i>

606
00:36:37,495 --> 00:36:38,758
Just move him.

607
00:36:38,830 --> 00:36:40,162
I wish I could.

608
00:36:40,298 --> 00:36:42,494
<i>Well, that's great, because
you know what you can do?</i>

609
00:36:42,567 --> 00:36:44,593
<i>You can move me.</i>

610
00:36:45,336 --> 00:36:47,328
<i>You don't know that
I have smallpox yet.</i>

611
00:36:47,439 --> 00:36:48,805
We have to assume.

612
00:36:48,907 --> 00:36:51,399
There's another isolation
room on the fifth floor.

613
00:36:51,476 --> 00:36:53,445
The problem is getting
him from here to there.

614
00:36:53,511 --> 00:36:54,740
So it's inconvenient?

615
00:36:54,846 --> 00:36:58,146
My having a fighting
chance at life is inconvenient?

616
00:37:00,652 --> 00:37:01,676
I'm sorry.

617
00:37:07,358 --> 00:37:08,951
We don't know
that he'll catch it.

618
00:37:09,027 --> 00:37:11,019
We don't know that
it's definitely smallpox,

619
00:37:11,129 --> 00:37:13,530
not until we get the DNA
results back from the CDC.

620
00:37:13,765 --> 00:37:15,461
What do you think
the dad just died of?

621
00:37:15,633 --> 00:37:17,192
Would it kill us
to talk it through?

622
00:37:17,302 --> 00:37:19,794
Kill us, no. Save
House, also no.

623
00:37:20,038 --> 00:37:22,701
Even if by some
miracle it's not smallpox,

624
00:37:22,774 --> 00:37:24,333
there's nothing
more for us to go on.

625
00:37:24,442 --> 00:37:26,638
There's no new data and
there isn't going to be any...

626
00:37:26,711 --> 00:37:27,735
Where are you going?

627
00:37:27,812 --> 00:37:29,610
To get more data.

628
00:37:31,382 --> 00:37:35,820
<i>"Gerritt seems
distant, preoccupied."</i>

629
00:37:35,954 --> 00:37:37,684
Who's Gerritt? Is he a slave?

630
00:37:38,223 --> 00:37:39,555
<i>Gerritt is the captain's kitty.</i>

631
00:37:39,657 --> 00:37:40,937
The captain's cat
is preoccupied?

632
00:37:40,992 --> 00:37:42,187
Skip the cat.

633
00:37:42,293 --> 00:37:45,354
<i>"One goat
slaughtered for dinner.</i>

634
00:37:45,430 --> 00:37:47,524
<i>"Broke out the next
barrel of wine..."</i>

635
00:37:47,665 --> 00:37:48,963
Skip the food.

636
00:37:49,033 --> 00:37:53,061
Can we go back to the
cat? Did the cat get sick?

637
00:37:53,304 --> 00:37:55,330
Smallpox is exclusive to humans.

638
00:37:55,406 --> 00:37:57,466
Ship captains didn't have pets.

639
00:37:57,542 --> 00:37:59,887
Nothing and nobody went on
those ships if it didn't have a purpose.

640
00:37:59,911 --> 00:38:01,402
Hunting mice and rats?

641
00:38:01,479 --> 00:38:02,674
For the crew.

642
00:38:02,747 --> 00:38:05,615
The hold was probably
infested with mice.

643
00:38:05,683 --> 00:38:06,883
What if that's the difference?

644
00:38:07,085 --> 00:38:09,350
What happened to Gerritt?

645
00:38:10,789 --> 00:38:11,813
Ah.

646
00:38:11,890 --> 00:38:14,553
Is that a sad "ah"
or a cute "ah"?

647
00:38:14,659 --> 00:38:17,254
Gerritt, he died.
It's a sad "ah."

648
00:38:19,664 --> 00:38:21,758
Before he died,
did he lose his fur?

649
00:38:25,603 --> 00:38:26,901
How did you know?

650
00:38:28,740 --> 00:38:30,140
Mice don't carry smallpox,

651
00:38:30,208 --> 00:38:31,904
but they do carry
rickettsialpox.

652
00:38:32,577 --> 00:38:33,772
Which is treatable.

653
00:38:36,414 --> 00:38:38,383
Just start them on doxycycline.

654
00:38:38,449 --> 00:38:40,941
Based on a bald cat? You
never heard of shedding?

655
00:38:41,052 --> 00:38:42,111
What's the downside?

656
00:38:42,220 --> 00:38:44,689
If we shove her full of
antibiotics plus the antivirals,

657
00:38:44,756 --> 00:38:46,418
it'll suppress her bone marrow.

658
00:38:46,524 --> 00:38:47,719
That girl's about to die.

659
00:38:47,792 --> 00:38:48,919
She probably is.

660
00:38:49,260 --> 00:38:51,422
And I don't want to risk
pushing her over the edge.

661
00:38:51,529 --> 00:38:53,088
At least look at the dad's body.

662
00:38:53,198 --> 00:38:57,192
Small patches of black
dead tissue will prove I'm right.

663
00:38:57,368 --> 00:39:01,066
Eschars appear with
rickettsialpox but not with smallpox.

664
00:39:01,139 --> 00:39:03,438
If he had developed
eschars, I would've noticed.

665
00:39:03,541 --> 00:39:05,772
You haven't been within
20 feet of the guy in hours.

666
00:39:06,277 --> 00:39:07,711
Have them check.

667
00:39:07,779 --> 00:39:10,510
Their job is to bleach
the body, kill the virus,

668
00:39:10,582 --> 00:39:12,342
and get it out of there
for Dr. House's sake.

669
00:39:12,784 --> 00:39:16,118
Bleaching the body will destroy
all evidence of rickettsialpox.

670
00:39:16,221 --> 00:39:18,884
There is no evidence.

671
00:39:19,123 --> 00:39:20,955
I'm not trying to
hurt anyone here.

672
00:39:21,092 --> 00:39:25,120
I'm not lying to you.
This is smallpox.

673
00:39:35,573 --> 00:39:38,065
House, you have
to examine the body.

674
00:39:38,743 --> 00:39:39,983
I'm not going anywhere near it.

675
00:39:40,478 --> 00:39:42,071
<i>Look for eschars. Hurry.</i>

676
00:39:43,414 --> 00:39:44,575
You think it's R-pox?

677
00:39:44,649 --> 00:39:47,676
<i>The Captain had a cat.
He lost his fur and then died.</i>

678
00:39:58,296 --> 00:40:00,094
<i>Step back, Dr. House.</i>

679
00:40:09,107 --> 00:40:11,338
It's kind of hard to do
an autopsy in oven mitts.

680
00:40:11,542 --> 00:40:12,635
<i>Take them off.</i>

681
00:40:12,710 --> 00:40:14,975
Says the woman standing
behind two panes of glass.

682
00:40:15,046 --> 00:40:16,139
<i>Do you believe me?</i>

683
00:40:17,115 --> 00:40:18,708
Forget me. Do you believe you?

684
00:40:18,816 --> 00:40:21,376
You think it's
rickettsialpox, don't you?

685
00:40:21,486 --> 00:40:24,718
<i>If it is, it's curable, and she's
gonna die unless we can prove it.</i>

686
00:40:30,328 --> 00:40:31,591
You really are annoying.

687
00:40:47,879 --> 00:40:49,211
Come on, House. Come on.

688
00:40:57,555 --> 00:40:58,853
Eschar.

689
00:41:03,795 --> 00:41:05,127
Eschars.

690
00:41:14,706 --> 00:41:17,767
<i>Start the girl on
doxycycline right now.</i>

691
00:41:36,461 --> 00:41:37,622
Mommy!

692
00:41:41,065 --> 00:41:43,057
You were good with her. - Yeah.

693
00:41:43,134 --> 00:41:44,568
Only after being bad.

694
00:41:44,635 --> 00:41:46,001
It takes practice.

695
00:41:47,271 --> 00:41:49,399
Maybe I should get a puppy.

696
00:41:49,674 --> 00:41:52,269
Yeah. Or pregnant.

697
00:42:01,753 --> 00:42:03,085
Hey.

698
00:42:06,524 --> 00:42:08,152
You're gonna be okay.

699
00:42:13,698 --> 00:42:14,757
Hey.

700
00:42:15,099 --> 00:42:16,123
Hey.

701
00:42:30,882 --> 00:42:32,282
Buy you breakfast?

702
00:42:32,350 --> 00:42:33,682
No, thanks.

703
00:42:35,153 --> 00:42:37,782
You can pay if it's starting
to feel like I'm carrying you.

704
00:42:37,855 --> 00:42:39,881
House, stop.

705
00:42:43,795 --> 00:42:45,889
When I was dying,

706
00:42:46,064 --> 00:42:48,465
you realized that
a little white lie

707
00:42:48,533 --> 00:42:50,866
between co-workers
wasn't such a big deal.

708
00:42:50,968 --> 00:42:55,838
Yeah, and that was true,
when you were dying.
